[3] Norovirus (suspected), hospital - UK (Wales)
Date: Mon 19 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: icwales.com, Mon 19 Jul 2004 [edited]
<http://icwales.icnetwork.co.uk/capitalcity/news/tm_objectid=14440783&method
=full&siteid=50082&headline=bug-forces-ward-isolation-at-uhw-name_page.html>

Wales: gastroenteritis outbreak closes hospital wards in Cardiff
-----------------------------------------------
An outbreak of gastroenteritis has forced the isolation of 2 wards at the
University Hospital of Wales, Cardiff. The wards have been shut to new
patients following an outbreak of diarrhea and vomiting among those already
being treated.
Hospital officials decided to close off the 2 wards yesterday [Sun 18 Jul
2004], which meant that no new patients would be admitted to the areas. A
hospital spokesman said that "we have cases of diarrhea and vomiting, and 2
wards have been affected. Normal precautions are being taken to combat the
outbreak."
He said that no patients were being transferred to other hospitals, and,
denied reports the virus infection had been brought into the wards via a
patient admitted with a contagious virus after returning from abroad. [As
in the report from Paisley, Scotland, the gastroenteritis outbreak in the
Cardiff hospital is presumed to be caused by norovirus infection. - Mod.CP]
