[4] Norovirus (suspected), hospitals - UK (England)
Date: Wed 21 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: BBC News, Thu 15 Jul 2004 [edited]
<http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/pr/fr/-/1/hi/england/somerset/3888345.stm>

England: gastroenteritis close wards in hospitals in Yeovil and Bristol
-----------------------------------------------
Wards have been closed at Yeovil District Hospital, and Bristol Royal
Infirmary (BRI), after an outbreak of a viral gastroenteritis. 2 wards at
the Yeovil district hospital were shut on Mon 12 Jul 2004, after patients
and staff showed symptoms of viral gastroenteritis. One ward was expected
to reopen on Thu 15 Jul 2004, and the other on the following Monday.
3 wards at the BRI were also closed after an outbreak of a similar illness.
One was later reopened. [Again, this outbreak is presumed to be a
consequence of norovirus infection, but, there is no laboratory
confirmation, although the disease struck more than one week ago. - Mod.CP]
